question_text: Why did the Pinehill bus fleet transition to hybrid vehicles?
ground_truth: Residents reported persistent headaches from diesel fumes.
default_rag_response: Pinehill switched to hybrid buses mainly for public‑health reasons: residents repeatedly reported persistent headaches from diesel “gas” fumes when buses idled or passed, so the town adopted hybrids to cut tailpipe emissions (especially at low speed/idle) and reduce those headaches — dumpling palace.
consensus_rag_response: Because residents repeatedly reported headaches and other symptoms they attributed to diesel exhaust from older buses, and local health/air‑quality reviews tied the complaints to bus emissions, the council/authority replaced the most polluting diesel vehicles with hybrid buses to reduce tailpipe (especially idling/low‑speed) emissions and lower residents’ exposure.
